    10	
    11	Status of this Memo
    12	
    13	   This handbook is the product of the Site Security Policy Handbook
    14	   Working Group (SSPHWG), a combined effort of the Security Area and
    15	   User Services Area of the Internet Engineering Task Force (IETF).
    16	   This FYI RFC provides information for the Internet community.  It
    17	   does not specify an Internet standard.  Distribution of this memo is
    18	   unlimited.
    19	
    20	Contributing Authors
    21	
    22	   The following are the authors of the Site Security Handbook.  Without
    23	   their dedication, this handbook would not have been possible.
    24	
    25	   Dave Curry (Purdue University), Sean Kirkpatrick (Unisys), Tom
    26	   Longstaff (LLNL), Greg Hollingsworth (Johns Hopkins University),
    27	   Jeffrey Carpenter (University of Pittsburgh), Barbara Fraser (CERT),
    28	   Fred Ostapik (SRI NISC), Allen Sturtevant (LLNL), Dan Long (BBN), Jim
    29	   Duncan (Pennsylvania State University), and Frank Byrum (DEC).
    30	
    31	Editors' Note
    32	
    33	   This FYI RFC is a first attempt at providing Internet users guidance
    34	   on how to deal with security issues in the Internet.  As such, this
    35	   document is necessarily incomplete.  There are some clear shortfalls;
    36	   for example, this document focuses mostly on resources available in
    37	   the United States.  In the spirit of the Internet's "Request for
    38	   Comments" series of notes, we encourage feedback from users of this
    39	   handbook.  In particular, those who utilize this document to craft
    40	   their own policies and procedures.
    41	
    42	   This handbook is meant to be a starting place for further research
    43	   and should be viewed as a useful resource, but not the final
    44	   authority.  Different organizations and jurisdictions will have
    45	   different resources and rules.  Talk to your local organizations,
    46	   consult an informed lawyer, or consult with local and national law
    47	   enforcement.  These groups can help fill in the gaps that this
    48	   document cannot hope to cover.
    49	
    50	
    51	
    52	Site Security Policy Handbook Working Group                     [Page 1]
    53	
    54	RFC 1244                 Site Security Handbook                July 1991
    55	
    56	
    57	   Finally, we intend for this FYI RFC to grow and evolve.  Please send
    58	   comments and suggestions to: ssphwg@cert.sei.cmu.edu.
