  2376	      3.9.7.3  Response Teams
  2377	
  2378	         Several organizations have formed special groups of people to
  2379	         deal with computer security problems.  These teams collect
  2380	         information about possible security holes and disseminate it to
  2381	         the proper people, track intruders, and assist in recovery from
  2382	         security violations.  The teams typically have both electronic
  2383	         mail distribution lists as well as a special telephone number
  2384	         which can be called for information or to report a problem.
  2385	         Many of these teams are members of the CERT System, which is
  2386	         coordinated by the National Institute of Standards and
  2387	         Technology (NIST), and exists to facilitate the exchange of
  2388	         information between the various teams.
  2389	
  2390	         3.9.7.3.1  DARPA Computer Emergency Response Team
  2391	
  2392	            The Computer Emergency Response Team/Coordination Center
  2393	            (CERT/CC) was established in December 1988 by the Defense
  2394	            Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA) to address
  2395	            computer security concerns of research users of the
  2396	            Internet.  It is operated by the Software Engineering
  2397	            Institute (SEI) at Carnegie-Mellon University (CMU).  The
  2398	            CERT can immediately confer with experts to diagnose and
  2399	            solve security problems, and also establish and maintain
  2400	            communications with the affected computer users and
  2401	
  2402	
  2403	
  2404	Site Security Policy Handbook Working Group                    [Page 43]
  2405	
  2406	RFC 1244                 Site Security Handbook                July 1991
  2407	
  2408	
  2409	            government authorities as appropriate.
  2410	
  2411	            The CERT/CC serves as a clearing house for the
  2412	            identification and repair of security vulnerabilities,
  2413	            informal assessments of existing systems, improvement of
  2414	            emergency response capability, and both vendor and user
  2415	            security awareness.  In addition, the team works with
  2416	            vendors of various systems in order to coordinate the fixes
  2417	            for security problems.
  2418	
  2419	            The CERT/CC sends out security advisories to the CERT-
  2420	            ADVISORY mailing list whenever appropriate.  They also
  2421	            operate a 24-hour hotline that can be called to report
  2422	            security problems (e.g., someone breaking into your system),
  2423	            as well as to obtain current (and accurate) information
  2424	            about rumored security problems.
  2425	
  2426	            To join the CERT-ADVISORY mailing list, send a message to
  2427	            CERT@CERT.SEI.CMU.EDU and ask to be added to the mailing
  2428	            list.  The material sent to this list also appears in the
  2429	            USENET newsgroup "comp.security.announce".  Past advisories
  2430	            are available for anonymous FTP from the host
  2431	            CERT.SEI.CMU.EDU.  The 24-hour hotline number is (412) 268-
  2432	            7090.
  2433	
  2434	            The CERT/CC also maintains a CERT-TOOLS list to encourage
  2435	            the exchange of information on tools and techniques that
  2436	            increase the secure operation of Internet systems.  The
  2437	            CERT/CC does not review or endorse the tools described on
  2438	            the list.  To subscribe, send a message to CERT-TOOLS-
  2439	            REQUEST@CERT.SEI.CMU.EDU and ask to be added to the mailing
  2440	            list.
  2441	
  2442	            The CERT/CC maintains other generally useful security
  2443	            information for anonymous FTP from CERT.SEI.CMU.EDU.  Get
  2444	            the README file for a list of what is available.
  2445	
  2446	            For more information, contact:
  2447	
  2448	               CERT
  2449	               Software Engineering Institute
  2450	               Carnegie Mellon University
  2451	               Pittsburgh, PA  15213-3890
  2452	
  2453	               (412) 268-7090
  2454	               cert@cert.sei.cmu.edu.
  2455	
