  2527	         3.9.7.3.4  DOE Computer Incident Advisory Capability (CIAC)
  2528	
  2529	            CIAC is the Department of Energy's (DOE's) Computer Incident
  2530	            Advisory Capability.  CIAC is a four-person team of computer
  2531	            scientists from Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory
  2532	            (LLNL) charged with the primary responsibility of assisting
  2533	            DOE sites faced with computer security incidents (e.g.,
  2534	            intruder attacks, virus infections, worm attacks, etc.).
  2535	            This capability is available to DOE sites on a 24-hour-a-day
  2536	            basis.
  2537	
  2538	            CIAC was formed to provide a centralized response capability
  2539	            (including technical assistance), to keep sites informed of
  2540	            current events, to deal proactively with computer security
  2541	            issues, and to maintain liaisons with other response teams
  2542	            and agencies.  CIAC's charter is to assist sites (through
  2543	            direct technical assistance, providing information, or
  2544	            referring inquiries to other technical experts), serve as a
  2545	            clearinghouse for information about threats/known
  2546	            incidents/vulnerabilities, develop guidelines for incident
  2547	            handling, develop software for responding to
  2548	            events/incidents, analyze events and trends, conduct
  2549	            training and awareness activities, and alert and advise
  2550	            sites about vulnerabilities and potential attacks.
  2551	
  2552	            CIAC's business hours phone number is (415) 422-8193 or FTS
  2553	            532-8193.  CIAC's e-mail address is CIAC@TIGER.LLNL.GOV.
  2554	
  2555	         3.9.7.3.5  NASA Ames Computer Network Security Response Team
  2556	
  2557	            The Computer Network Security Response Team (CNSRT) is NASA
