  5246	   [REYNOLDS89]
  5247	           The Helminthiasis of the Internet, RFC 1135,
  5248	           USC/Information Sciences Institute, Marina del Rey,
  5249	           CA, December 1989.
  5250	
  5251	           This report looks back at the helminthiasis (infestation
  5252	           with, or disease caused by parasitic worms) of the
  5253	           Internet that was unleashed the evening of 2 November 1988.
  5254	           This document provides a glimpse at the infection,its
  5255	           festering, and cure.  The impact of the worm on the Internet
  5256	           community, ethics statements, the role of the news media,
  5257	
  5258	
  5259	
  5260	Site Security Policy Handbook Working Group                    [Page 94]
  5261	
  5262	RFC 1244                 Site Security Handbook                July 1991
  5263	
  5264	
  5265	           crime in the computer world, and future prevention is
  5266	           discussed.  A documentation review presents four publications
  5267	           that describe in detail this particular parasitic computer
  5268	           program.  Reference and bibliography sections are also
  5269	           included.  Available on-line on host ftp.nisc.sri.com
  5270	           directory rfc, filename rfc1135.txt.  Also available on
  5271	           host nis.nsf.net, directory RFC, filename RFC1135.TXT-1.
  5272	
  5273	   [SEELEY89]
