  5277	
  5278	           Details are presented as a "walk thru" of this particular
  5279	           worm program.  The paper opened with an abstract,
  5280	           introduction, detailed chronology of events upon the
  5281	           discovery of the worm, an overview, the internals of the
  5282	           worm, personal opinions, and conclusion.
  5283	
  5284	   [SPAFFORD88]
  5285	           Spafford, E., "The Internet Worm Program: An
  5286	           Analysis", Computer Communication Review, Vol. 19,
  5287	           No. 1, ACM SIGCOM, January 1989.  Also issued as Purdue
  5288	           CS Technical Report CSD-TR-823, 28 November 1988.
  5289	
  5290	           Describes the infection of the Internet as a worm
  5291	           program that exploited flaws in utility programs in
  5292	           UNIX based systems.  The report gives a detailed
  5293	           description of the components of the worm program:
  5294	           data and functions.  Spafford focuses his study on two
  5295	           completely independent reverse-compilations of the
  5296	           worm and a version disassembled to VAX assembly language.
